6.00SC | Introduction to Computer Science and Programming (Spring 2011) | http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/electrical-engineering-and-computer-science/6-00sc-introduction-to-computer-science-and-programming-spring-2011 | textbook:Guttag, John. Introduction to Computation and Programming Using Python. Spring 2013 edition. MIT Press, 2013. textbook:Guttag, John. Introduction to Computation and Programming Using Python: With Application to Understanding Data. MIT Press, 2016. level:Undergraduate instructors:John Guttag term:Spring 2011 features:Video lectures, Captions/transcript, Online textbooks, Assignments: problem sets with solutions, Assignments: programming with examples, Exams and solutions, Recitation videos, Resource Index description:This subject is aimed at students with little or no programming experience. It aims to provide students with an understanding of the role computation can play in solving problems. It also aims to help students, regardless of their major, to feel justifiably confident of their ability to write small programs that allow them to accomplish useful goals. The class will use the Python programming language.
